    "meta": {},
    "html": "<!-- TODO(legacy-link-migration): This file contains legacy outlinks to *.cs.sun.ac.za / www.cs.sun.ac.za. Replace with internal routes or pass through the legacy-link resolver once mapping rules are finalized. -->\n\n<h2>Contact details</h2>\n<h3>Postal address</h3>\n<p>Computer Science Division,<br>Dept of Mathematical Sciences,<br>Stellenbosch University<br>Private Bag X1, 7602 Matieland, SOUTH AFRICA</p>\n<h3>Physical address</h3>\n<p>Computer Science,<br>Stellenbosch University<br>Decanting Facility, Hammanshand Road<br>7600 Stellenbosch, SOUTH AFRICA</p>\n<h3>Telephone and Fax</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Telephone: +27 21 808 4232</li>\n<li>Fax: +27 86 603 7130</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Enquiries</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Administrative enquiries: <code>secretary@cs.sun.ac.za</code></li>\n<li>Post-graduate enquiries: <code>postgrad@cs.sun.ac.za</code></li>\n<li>Under-graduate enquiries: <code>undergrad@cs.sun.ac.za</code></li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Want to pay us a visit?</h2>\n<p>The department is currently located on the fifth floor of the General Engineering building.</p>\n<h3>Google Maps</h3>\n<p>Our geographic coordinates are <a href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/place/33%C2%B055'30.9%22S+18%C2%B051'55.1%22E\">33° 55′ 30.90″ South 18° 51′ 55.10″ East</a></p>\n<h2>Also...</h2>\n<p>Here is a QR code for our website.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/cs-assets/qr.png\" alt=\"Computer Science QR code\"></p>\n",
